<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title><%= @repo %></title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h2><%= @repo %></h2>
    <p>To use this repo on your site, add the following lines to your pacman.conf:</p>
    <pre style="border-style: solid;border-width: thin;display:inline-block;padding: 10px;">[amylum]
SigLevel = Required
Server = https://repo.scrtybybscrty.org</pre>
    <p>You'll need to add my GPG key to pacman's keyring so that pacman can verify the package and repo signatures.</p>
    <pre style="border-style: solid;border-width: thin;display:inline-block;padding: 10px;">pacman-key --recv-key 0xBC5F2A0543D0048F
pacman-key --lsign 0xBC5F2A0543D0048F</pre>
    <p>Here are a couple places you can use to verify the above key:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://keybase.io/akerl">Keybase</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://onename.com/akerl">Onename</a></li>
      <li><a href="http://blog.akerl.org/gpg.txt">My blog</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>This repo is build and served by <a href="https://github.com/amylum">these open source repos</a></p>
    <h4>Metadata:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/repo.db">repo.db</a> -- (<a href="/repo.db.sig">sig</a>)</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Packages:</h4>
    <ul>
      <% @packages.each do |package| %>
        <li><a href="/<%= package.key %>"><%= package.key %></a> -- (<a href="/<%= package.key %>.sig">sig</a>)</li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  </body>
</html>
